Two years ago it was illegal to hunt in Indiana with a rifle like this.
 Last year Indiana changed the casing length to 1.8 inches.  I have a gunsmith
 CF Gunworks LLC  that took  the 350 Remington Magnum  and shortened that casing to 1.8 inches
 Which is what this cartridge now is. You can’t  buy this ammo or the gun ,they 
 have to be custom made which is why they are expensive. The .357 and .44 magnums are just another example of Indiana Deer Legal cartridges that you can use. This is a High Powered Rifle that has been modified to meet Indiana specs and requirements . This rifle is 100 % legal to hunt with in Indiana .
Don’t wait for Deer season to decide you want one, you won’t be able to. This is someone’s chance to own
a very nice Indiana Deer Legal High Powered Rifle of which only a hand full are available.

I have a custom built Remington Model 700 That was a 350 Remington Magnum
it has been shortened to 1.8 inch. Indiana Deer Legal casing
the factory barrel has been bedded and set back to shorten the chamber.
It comes with Redding Dies that have been ground to match. 
I have brass and about 30rds of ammo that was made by C F Gunworks.
It is toped off with a leupold 3x9.
This rifle killed 3 deer at over 300yds this past season. It is amazing!!
I would like $1600 with scope or $1400 without.

This Rifle was custom built to Indiana Specs!!!!! And is referred to as a 350 JR
 This cartridge is modeled after the Remington 350 Magnum. They shorten the case
 to 1.8 inches, I took a picture so you can see the cartridge, bullet is 200grn
and clearly meets Indiana guide lines. I hope this helps with the confusion. 
Certain rifles like the .357 magnum or .44 magnum can be bought at walmart
and are perfectly legal. Indiana says you can't go below .357 magnum. This rifle can't
be bought at WalMart they have to be custom made which the price reflects

The new Gen4 has several new features designed to satisfy the most demanding consumers. It is based on a full size G17/G22 MBS (multiple back straps) frame with a reduced short frame trigger mechanism housing. The multiple back strap system allows the user to change the circumference of the grip to fit their individual hand size.  The grip has three options; a short frame version, medium frame or large frame that are easily changed and secured with a single pin. The grip angle of the GLOCK “Safe Action” Pistol is not changed by back strap modifications. This ensures that the shooter does not shoot high or low when modifying the back strap or when shooting with a different GLOCK Pistol. 

The smallest back strap is integrated in the GLOCK MBS Frame reducing the trigger distance of the standard size frame by 2 mm. The medium back strap is a 2 mm back strap offering equal size of a standard frame. The large back strap is a 4 mm back strap.

The magazine release catch of the Gen4 is reversible and enlarged. The reversible magazine allows users to switch the catch to the left or right side of the pistol with no additional parts.

Additionally, the Gen4 has a new Rough Textured Frame (Gen4 RTF) surface designed to enhance grip traction and is present on the frame as well as the interchangeable back straps.

Internally, the original recoil spring has been replaced with a dual recoil spring assembly. The dual recoil spring assembly noticeably reduces the recoil while simultaneously increasing the life cycle of the assembly.

postcontent:
The GG&G A2 Style BUIS (Back Up Iron Sight) provides the operator with an easy-to-install and easy-to-operate flip up rear sight, and includes the all important locking detent. The A2 BUIS is always at the tactical ready once placed in the up position. The sight cannot be folded down without depressing the spring assisted detent release button located on the left side of the sight base. This totally eliminates the possibility of accidentally lowering the sight.

The A2 BUIS can be used as a stand-alone sight or in conjunction with one of our interface rails. The A2 BUIS can be used as a co-witness iron sight with most red dot sighting systems. Weighing in at just over two ounces, this sight features the standard military A2-style double peep aperture which allows for end user known point of impact. The sight has full windage adjustment with standard military windage knob and windage screw. No need to retrain when using this sight. One click of the windage knob provides approximately 0.48 MOA change when mounted on the M16A2E4 rifle and about 0.65 MOA on the M4 carbine. Initial zero is set by adjusting the weapons front sight post. It is low profile so that when in the down position, it will clear most optics. The mount body and sight stem are manufactured from billet 6061 T6 aluminum alloy and Type III hard coat anodized in a non-reflective black mil spec finish to provide combat durability. All steel components are black manganese phosphated per mil spec. Used by elite armed forces and law enforcement teams word wide.

title: For Sale:  Adam Arms 16" Tactical Evo Upper
location: Western Suburbs, Minneapolis / St. Paul, Minnesota
postcontent:
High quality Adams Arms piston upper, I've never had a problem with it and it has cycled everything I have fed it including TulAmmo, mil spec ammo and match grade ammo without a problem. It's more accurate than I am and has been incredibly reliable. 

The handguard is a 12" Samson Evolution Modular Rail Free Float Handguard and comes with a 4" and 2" picatiny rail section and a QD sling swivel adapter. I'm also including a bipod stud from Samson Manufacturing that sits flush with the rail, no bulky adapter required. As a result you can leave the bipod stud in at all times without any distractions  and no extra weight.  

The barrel, bolt carrier, and piston system have a proprietary QPQ Melonite treatment which keeps the chamber clean and cool even when using dirty ammunition. The proprietary QPQ Melonite treatment to the barrel provides an extremely hard, slick surface on the steel that resists carbon adhesion and increases corrosion, extending a barrel's service life by reducing friction produced during firing. Also, the treatment converts the barrel steel's surface without any build-up, retaining all of the benefits of traditional chrome lining without suffering the accuracy degradation commonly encountered due to uneven application of chrome inside the barrel's bore. The end result is a barrel that's capable of producing accuracy on par with a match stainless steel tube, while also exhibiting the longevity and resilience of a chrome lined, mil-spec barrel. 

The midlength piston system will give you the benefits of a longer forearm by giving the user a longer, more ergonomic grip, a longer sight radius between the front and the rear sight for quicker sight acquisition and less felt recoil.

All this combined with the Adams Arms piston system and you'll have an upper that will run cleaner, cooler, and longer than any other AR upper you own.

title: For Sale:  Permit to Carry Training
postcontent:
Permit to Carry Class $75.00
May 3rd in Dodge Center
Signup at precisionplusfirearms.com or text/call REDACTED

Why should you get a Permit to Carry?
You should get one so that you can defend yourself and loved ones from the numerous "bad guys" out there that prey on the law abiding citizens. Most violent encounters are over within a minute and the typical police response is greater than 5 minutes. Some people believe that the only people that get a Permit to Carry are "gun nuts" or "wanna be cops" That is far from the truth. People who get their Permit to Carry are regular people that want to be able to take responsibility for their own safety and security. They are Doctors, Lawyers, blue collar workers, bankers, computer programmers, accountants, retirees and housewives.
Gun Ownership is a serious responsibility and the use of deadly force is a very serious matter and so is protecting yourself and loved ones. Do you know what Minnesota's Use of Force Laws are? Even if you do not want to get your Permit to Carry or even carry a firearm, you should still get training in the safe handling of firearms and the laws of self-defense.

If you need a gun for the shooting portion of the class I will have guns available for free. 

This class is good for the Minnesota Permit to Carry and also Florida, Arizona, Maine, Idaho, Kansas, Oklahoma, Iowa, Wisconsin and Michigan Non resident permits.
With the Minnesota Permit to Carry you are legal to carry in up to 23 States. With the Non-Resident Permits you could get up to 35 states.

title: For Sale:  Stunning Kimber Model 82G for Sale
location: Dunn, Raleigh / Durham / CH, North Carolina
postcontent:
Kimber model 82G...   the best government waste ever!   US Gov't ordered 20,000 of these precision target rifles for smallbore competition.   They then left them in the packaging until someone decided to inventory them by slashing open the package with a razor knife.   This is the signature of the kimber 82G is a thin razor-groove cut in the stock. 

The 82G is a single-shot, 1-in-16 twist, Heavy Competition barrel (25") bolt action firearm.  It was built to the standard of being sub-MOA rifles.  The butt stock is adjustable for Length of Pull and all spacers are included.  stock is walnut and has some beautiful tiger-striping that doesn't really show in the pictures.   Sling swivel is adjustable to the shooter.  SIghts are anschutz at 1/5MOA per click.  Trigger is factory set for 3.5 lbs but is fully adjustable for takeup,  pullweight and overtravel.   It breaks like glass.

If you are looking to get into smallbore competitive shooting, this is simply the least expensive way to get in without dumping 1400 bucks into the lower-end anschutz rifles. 

This rifle is UNFIRED.   It was bought as new (non-rusty) from the CMP when they still had these.  The stock HAS NO CUT IN IT.   This one was hand selected from the South Store in Anniston.  The finish and stock are flawless.   This rifle is unfired as I own several comp smallbore rifles.  I brought it home,  gave it a complete disassembly,  cleaned it thoroughly and put it back in the safe.   My photo skills don't do it justice.
